    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mixing It Up</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dina Schlesinger letter on June 3 article about classical music concert halls says new programming would attract younger listeners (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Concert Hall? How About Music Museum? [June 3]:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Concert Hall? How About Music Museum? [June 3]:</p>
        <p>In Lawrence Kramer's wonderful article he compares the sedentary nature of a concert hall with the lively interaction of a museum. Just as a Leonardo drawing may be a room away from a Basquiat print in a museum, a Beethoven symphony could be followed by a Stevie Wonder song in a concert hall. It would be refreshing to hear concertgoers snapping their fingers, and a program like that might expose younger listeners to Beethoven.</p>
        <p>Dina Schlesinger  New York, N.Y.</p>
        <p>WHY CLASSICAL MATTERS</p>
      </block>
